verbose_text: We have earlier also shown that TNF levels do not predict response to TNFi treatment in AS [XREF_BIBR], but given the increased levels of TNF mRNA in sacroiliac joints [XREF_BIBR], it can be argued that there is no or only limited overflow of site specific inflammation markers in AS similar to the lack of specific biomarkers found in rheumatoid arthritis [XREF_BIBR].
